text.tspan: Thank you for trying out Kibojoe Linux and we hope you
enjoy it. If you have any questions or any other problems,
please contact us in our forum and or the IRC, we will be
glad to help you!
THANK YOU!
Thank You!
Kibojoe has several CLI tools. The Pacli-SysClean to
manage your packages and JWMConf to work with the
JWM settings files. Other CLI tools are also available.
KiboJoe is light and elegant. Tons of the latest free
open source software to fit your needs, it has all the
convenience to download from multiple resources.
Kibojoe Linux is a Manjaro Linux re-spin with Joe's Window
Manager (JWM). JWM is a light weight window manager to
run on the X11 Window System. JWM makes a good window
manager for older computers and less powerful systems.
Welcome to Kibojoe Linux!
Kibojoe is created with the "Manjaro-Tools" and maintained
collaboratively. During the installation, this slide-show will
provide a quick introduction. The installation wouldn't take
that long but thanks for your patience.
